BSO, II, 250-51 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Isaiah of Aleppo was a saint said to be the last survivor of the disciples of Mar Awgin, and some traditions attribute the composition of the life of Awgin to him. Isaiah and his wife never touched, living together in continence. He travelled throughout Mesopotamia and converted 3000 Marcionites.</note>
